rranges for Jack, Kate and Hurley to join the Dharma Initiative. Sayid is found by Jin, however, he is forced to pretend he is an Other and is subsequently imprisoned by Dharma. In 2007, following the crash of Flight 316, Sun and Frank learn from Christian Shephard that the other survivors are trapped in the past.\n |LineColor= 69D0E3\n }}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Lost (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber=96\n |EpisodeNumber2=10\n |Title=[[He's Our You]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2009|3|25}}\n |DirectedBy=[[Greg Yaitanes]]\n |WrittenBy=Edward Kitsis & Adam Horowitz\n |Aux2=[[Sayid Jarrah|Sayid]]\n |Viewers=8.82<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/03/26/wednesday-ratings-american-idol-strong-lost-low/15224/ |title=Wednesday Ratings: American Idol strong, Lost low |publisher=TV by the Numbers |author=Seidman, Robert |date=March 26, 2009 |accessdate=October 28, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121009072444/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/03/26/wednesday-ratings-american-idol-strong-lost-low/15224/ |archivedate=October 9, 2012 }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=In 1977, Sayid does not cooperate with Sawyer and members of the Dharma Initiative vote to execute Sayid. A 12-year-old Ben frees Sayid in his effort to join the Others. However, once they have escaped, Sayid shoots Ben. In flashbacks, Sayid is caught by Ilana, a bounty hunter, who has been hired to take him to Guam.\n |LineColor= 69D0E3\n }}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Lost (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber=97\n |EpisodeNumber2=11\n |Title=[[Whatever Happened, Happened]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2009|4|1}}\n |DirectedBy=[[Bobby Roth]]\n |WrittenBy=Carlton Cuse & Damon Lindelof\n |Aux2=Kate\n |Viewers=9.35<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/04/02/wednesday-ratings-american-idol-and-lost-lead-night/15780/ |title=Wednesday Ratings: American Idol and Lost lead night |publisher=TV by the Numbers |author=Seidman, Robert |date=April 2, 2009 |accessdate=Octo