3 }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=In 1988, Jin and Rousseau's team are attacked by the smoke monster on their way to the radio tower. Charlotte confesses that she grew up on the island before dying. John Locke leaves the island by turning the wheel in the frozen chamber. Off the island, Ben brings Jack and Sun to Eloise Hawking, Daniel's mother, at the same time that Desmond finds her.\n |LineColor= 69D0E3\n }}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Lost (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber=92\n |EpisodeNumber2=6<ref name=switch>\"[[316 (Lost)|316]]\" and \"[[The Life and Death of Jeremy Bentham]]\" were aired out of order from their original scheduling. This was purposefully changed by Damon Lindelof and Carlton Cuse. {{cite podcast|url=http://ll.media.abc.com/podcast/audio/itunes/LOST_507_audio_podcast_5877ab2e-0c3b-4f8d-a475-b234416259b8_1983897.mp3 |title=The Official LOST Audio Podcast: February 12th, 2009 |website=[[American Broadcasting Company]] (ABC.com). |host=[[Carlton Cuse|Cuse, Carlton]]; [[Damon Lindelof|Lindelof, Damon]] |date=February 12, 2009 |accessdate=February 12, 2009 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090319222556/http://ll.media.abc.com/podcast/audio/itunes/LOST_507_audio_podcast_5877ab2e-0c3b-4f8d-a475-b234416259b8_1983897.mp3 |archivedate=March 19, 2009 }}</ref>\n |Title=[[316 (Lost)|316]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2009|2|18}}\n |DirectedBy=Stephen Williams\n |WrittenBy=Damon Lindelof & Carlton Cuse\n |Aux2= [[Jack Shephard|Jack]]\n |Viewers=11.27<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/02/19/wednesday-ratings-american-idol-and-lost-shine/13087/ |title=Wednesday Ratings: American Idol and LOST shine |publisher=TV by the Numbers |author=Seidman, Robert |date=February 19, 2009 |accessdate=October 28, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131008222911/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/02/19/wednesday-ratings-american-idol-and-lost-shine/13087/ |archivedate=October 8, 2013 }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=Eloise Hawking tells the Oceanic Six how to return to the island. Jack, Kate, Hurley, Sun, Sayid, and Ben board Ajira Airways Flight 316, which is piloted by Frank Lapidus, with Locke's body. After a flash of white light on the plane, Jin finds Jack, Kate and Hurley back on the island.\n |LineColor= 69D0E3\n }}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Lost (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber=93\n |EpisodeNumber2=7<ref name=switch/>\n |Title=[[The Life and Death of Jeremy Bentham]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2009|2|25}}\n |DirectedBy=Jack Bender\n |WrittenBy=Carlton Cuse & Damon Lindelof\n |Aux2= [[John Locke (Lost)|Locke]]\n |Viewers=9.82<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/02/26/wednesday-american-idol-dominates-lost-and-the-lowlifes/13570/ |title=Wednesday: American Idol dominates, Lost and the lowLifes |publisher=TV by the Numbers |author=Seidman, Robert |date=February 26, 2009 |accessdate=October 28, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131008231946/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/02/26/wednesday-american-idol-dominates-lost-and-the-lowlifes/13570/ |archivedate=October 8, 2013 }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=Locke, who is suddenly alive following the crash of Flight 316 on the island, is questioned by the other survivors and finds Ben among the injured. In flashback, Locke's off-island mission to reunite the Oceanic Six and return them to the island is aided by Charles Widmore and Matthew Abaddon before Ben murders Locke.\n |LineColor= 69D0E3\n }}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Lost (season 5)\n |EpisodeNumber=94\n |EpisodeNumber2=8\n |Title=[[LaFleur (Lost)|LaFleur]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2009|3|4}}\n |DirectedBy=Mark Goldman\n |WrittenBy=Elizabeth Sarnoff & [[Kyle Pennington]]\n |Aux2=[[James \"Sawyer\" Ford|Sawyer]]\n |Viewers=10.61<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/03/05/wednesday-ratings-americas-next-top-model-premieres-well-with-young-women/13987/ |title=Wednesday: America's Next Top Model premieres well 