rding the cylinder's location, and learns its placement through the ideas Peter has absorbed from his father through [[osmosis]]. The man takes him to a cemetery housing tombstones bearing the names of Peter and his mother and finds the cylinder. Olivia shows up after learning the location from Walter and kills the man. The object burrows back underground before either side can discover its purpose. Peter encounters the Observer, who demonstrates [[telepathy|telepathic]] abilities before shooting Peter with a yet unknown weapon. At the end of the episode, Olivia, who is standing in the kitchen, sees John Scott standing in the kitchen entrance.\n |LineColor = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Fringe (season 1)\n |EpisodeNumber = 5\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 5\n |Title = [[Power Hungry (Fringe)|Power Hungry]]\n |DirectedBy = [[Christopher Misiano]]\n |WrittenBy = [[Jason Cahill]] & [[Julia Cho]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2008|10|14}}\n |ProdCode = 3T7654\n |Viewers = 9.16<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2008/10/21/top-fox-primetime-shows-october-13-19/6672 |title=Top Fox Primetime Shows, October 13\u201319 |first=Bill |last=Gorman |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=October 21, 2008 |accessdate=December 5, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120921092736/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2008/10/21/top-fox-primetime-shows-october-13-19/6672/ |archivedate=September 21, 2012 }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = The team discovers a man, Joseph Meegar ([[Ebon Moss-Bachrach]]), with the uncontrolled ability to affect electrical energy, made the way he is by a scientist performing illegal [[human subject research|experiments on humans]]. With the help of carrier pigeons modified to track the man's electromagnetic signature, the team manages to track him down and arrest the scientist. Meanwhile, Olivia begins seeing visions of John, which she learns are caused by memories transferred to her during their experience in the first episode. Through these memories, she discovers one of John's secret hideouts, where a large number of investigation files relating to the Pattern are found.\n |LineColor = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Fringe (season 1)\n |EpisodeNumber = 6\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 6\n |Title = [[The Cure (Fringe)|The Cure]]\n |DirectedBy = [[Bill Eagles]]\n |WrittenBy = [[Felicia D. Henderson]] & [[Brad Caleb Kane]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2008|10|21}}\n |ProdCode = 3T7655\n |Viewers = 8.91<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2008/10/29/top-fox-primetime-shows-october-20-26/7126 |title=Top Fox Primetime Shows, October 20\u201326 |first=Robert |last=Seidman |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=October 29, 2008 |accessdate=December 5, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120201214252/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2008/10/29/top-fox-primetime-shows-october-20-26/7126/ |archivedate=February 1, 2012 }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = A woman (Maria Dizzia) with a [[lupus]] like [[autoimmune disease]] known as \"Bellini's lymphocemia\" is kidnapped and given a drug that makes her brain emit a multi-[[gigawatt]] [[radio-frequency|RF]] burst, cooking her and the patrons of a diner she stumbles into to death. When the team investigates, they find that another woman (Marjan Neshat) with the same rare disease has been kidnapped. After talking to the doctor who was treating them, Olivia learns that the chief scientist of a competitor of Massive Dynamic is the one who gave her the drug. Peter makes a deal with Nina Sharp, who tells him where to find the second victim before she can be turned into a terrorist weapon.\n |LineColor = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Fringe (season 1)\n |EpisodeNumber = 7\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 7\n |Title = [[In Which We Meet Mr. Jones]]\n |DirectedBy = [[Brad Anderson (director)|Brad Anderson]]\n |WrittenBy = J. J. Abrams & Jeff Pinkner\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2008|11|11}}\n |ProdCode = 3T7656\n |Viewers = 8.61<ref>{{cite web |