sm|monotheistic]] [[cult]] activities expand, sparking political discord at the [[Quorum of Twelve (Battlestar Galactica)|Quorum of Twelve]], and possibly a religious civil war, while [[Saul Tigh|Colonel Tigh's]] mental state again becomes fragile.\n |LineColor = 7DBAD9\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Battlestar Galactica (season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 60\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 5\n |Title = [[The Road Less Traveled (Battlestar Galactica)|The Road Less Traveled]]\n |DirectedBy = Michael Rymer\n |WrittenBy = [[Mark Verheiden]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2008|5|2}}\n |Aux4 = 39,676\n |ShortSummary = Starbuck faces mutiny on board the ''Demetrius'' when she expresses her intent in cooperating with the Cylon [[Leoben Conoy|Leoben]], who has boarded the ship to help her find Earth.\n |LineColor = 7DBAD9\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Battlestar Galactica (season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 61\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 6\n |Title = [[Faith (Battlestar Galactica)|Faith]]\n |DirectedBy = Michael Nankin\n |WrittenBy = Seamus Kevin Fahey\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2008|5|9}}\n |Aux4 = 39,675\n |ShortSummary = Starbuck leads a mission to see the Cylon Hybrid who reveals more clues to finding Earth. On ''Galactica'', [[Laura Roslin|President Roslin]] discusses religious faith with a dying woman named Emily.\n |LineColor = 7DBAD9\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Battlestar Galactica (season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 62\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 7\n |Title = [[Guess What's Coming to Dinner?]]\n |DirectedBy = Wayne Rose\n |WrittenBy = Michael Angeli\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2008|5|16}}\n |Aux4 = 39,673\n |ShortSummary = Bitter enemies must set aside their grudges as the ''Demetrius'' crew teams up with Cylon rebels to destroy a vital enemy target.\n |LineColor = 7DBAD9\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Battlestar Galactica (season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 63\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 8\n |Title = [[Sine Qua Non (Battlestar Galactica)|Sine Qua Non]]\n |DirectedBy = [[Rod Hardy]]\n |WrittenBy = Michael Taylor\n |